    "In our research, P = {P1, P2, • • •, Pn} is assumed to be a set of competing products of different brands.",
    "For each product Pi, the attribute-grained preference analysis task is described as follows: The sentiment polarity Y is predicted over the full set of target-aspect pairs{(t, a): t ∈ T, a ∈ A} given the reviews in D1, a set of target entities T and a fixed aspect set A.",
    "Design features refer to the tangible and measurable characteristics of a product.",
